archimate:BusinessObject.name: MACAddressValue
archimate:BusinessObject.documentation:
"This class is used to define a list of MAC addresses and MAC address range values as an unordered list of strings, each specifying a MAC address or a range of MAC addresses according to the canonical 802 MAC address format. Each string entry is either:
- a single MAC address, such as 0000:00A5:0000 - a range of MAC addresses specified by an address and mask, such as 0000:00A5:0000,FFFF:FFFF:0000, which defines a range of MAC addresses in which the first four octets are equal to 0000:00A5. "
